  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of fiduciary duty by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, several mitigating circumstances warrant leniency. The defendant has no prior criminal record, indicating a low risk of recidivism, and has made active efforts towards restitution by partially paying back the stolen funds. Considering these factors, a sentence of 6 months of incarceration, accompanied by a mandate for full restitution during supervised release, is sufficient to address the gravity of the offense while encouraging rehabilitation.",
